        "id": 1118104
      },
      "writtenOn": "2020-09-15T02:08:26Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I don\u0027t see why that\u0027s a problem as long as the UI shows that only unexpected results are kept after a certain time.\n\nI am thinking that maybe we don\u0027t restrict queries into the past or into the future. This could be used to check that we are purging results correctly, and we also shouldn\u0027t have results in the future, so we should be able to query both and ensure that they have 0 results. WDYT?",
